HEADWORD: nonstarter
<hw>nonstarter</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a person with a
record of failing.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> loser, failure, unsuccessful person.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A horse that fails to run in a race for which it has
been entered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A proposal that will not receive serious
consideration by those with authority to decide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

